programme.desc: As each day begins get the facts you need to stay informed. Bridget Brennan and James Glenday present the latest news, overnight developments and today's top stories, joined by Emma Rebellato, Catherine Murphy and Nate Byrne.

programme.title: ABC News Mornings
programme.desc: Stay in the know with what's happening this morning. ABC News brings you up-to-the-minute news to fuel your daily conversations so you can stay connected and follow the discussion across the day. Presented by Gemma Veness.

programme.title: ABC News At Noon
programme.desc: The leading news at lunchtime. Ros Childs brings you the day's top stories and the latest news as it unfolds, with reporters in the community across Australia and around the world reporting on the issues that matter to you.

programme.title: Landline: Mekong Special
programme.desc: Landline visits South-East Asia where a unique charity in Cambodia gives cows to farmers in return for sending their children to school. In Laos a dairy's buffalo rental scheme is helping lift families out of poverty.

programme.title: Four Corners
programme.desc: The multi-award winning Four Corners returns for another year of powerhouse investigative journalism - fearless and forensic, exposing scandals, triggering inquiries, leading debate and holding power to account for 65 years.

programme.title: Media Watch
programme.desc: Australia's leading forum for media analysis and comment. Host Linton Besser, a four-time Walkley award-winning investigative reporter and former foreign correspondent, brings you a fearless critique of the week's journalism.

programme.title: Secret Science
programme.desc: Matt Okine discovers that when it comes to making babies, it's not always easy. He's surprised to learn in the last 40 years, men's sperm count has dropped by 50%. So what men can do to improve that number? (Part 1)

programme.title: Grand Designs Australia
programme.desc: Richard and Erin Sims start out building a farm-style lodge, however it balloons into a building of epic proportions, complete with three 'wings', seven-metre-high chimneys, and thousands of hand-picked dolerite stones.

programme.title: Dream Gardens
programme.desc: Paul and Zoe want a garden to match their fabulous art deco home in Melbourne. But project managing the ambitious build themselves will take courage. Loved ones think they're crazy, can they prove the doubters wrong? (Final)

programme.title: Iconic Australia
programme.desc: Australia is a mining nation. The digging started when gold was discovered in 185. 170 years later, it is a massively profitable export industry. The challenge is balancing, money, power, culture and the environment.

programme.title: ABC News with Joe O'Brien
programme.desc: Joe O'Brien brings you a comprehensive summary of the day's events, with the latest breaking news, in depth coverage of the top stories, live crosses, interviews and explainers to bring you up to speed on what's going on.

programme.title: The Cook Up With Adam Liaw
programme.desc: Adam gives his guests, chefs Gunjan Aylawadi and Nagesh Seethiah, the mission of five dollar per-head dinners in fifteen minutes or less.

programme.title: That Pacific Sports Show
programme.desc: Join Tiana Penitani Gray and Sam Wykes for your weekly hit of Pacific joy, as they share inspiring stories and incredible sporting prowess of athletes with Pacific Island heritage, from Australia and around the world.

programme.title: ABC National News
programme.desc: There's never been a more important time for transparency and trust. ABC News brings you the day's top stories and latest news, with more reporters to tell you what's going on and why it matters. Presented by Joe O'Brien.

programme.title: Ep02: Sol Campbell : PL Moments
programme.desc: Premier League Moments sits down with one of the most dominant centre-backs the league has ever seen. Sol Campbell rose through the ranks at Tottenham Hotspur before making one of the most controversial moves in Premier League history, when he crossed the divide to join rivals Arsenal. Under Arsene Wenger, Campbell became a cornerstone of the defence, winning two league titles and playing a vital role in the Invincibles season. From crunching tackles to towering goals, we look back on the defining moments of a 19-year career.

programme.title: Ep25: Sol Campbell - The Move That Shook North London : PL Stories
programme.desc: Ahead of the first North London derby of the season, we sit down with the man who made one of most controversial transfers in World football; Sol Campbell. He opens up about his decision to leave Tottenham for their fiercest rivals, Arsenal, the intense pressure of returning to White Hart Lane that first season, and how he's dealt with the fallout ever since. A fascinating insight into the 'move that shook North London'.

programme.title: Ep27: Tijjani Reijnders : The Big Interview
programme.desc: Nine years ago, Tijjani Reijnders was stacking shelves at a local supermarket. Now, after lighting up Serie A with AC Milan, the Dutch international is making a name for himself with Manchester City in the Premier League. This week, The Big Interview sits down with Reijnders to discuss his journey from Zwolle in the Netherlands to the Etihad via AZ Alkmaar and the San Siro. Reijnders reflects on his Indonesian heritage, the influence of his father on his career and adapting to the Premier League.

programme.title: Ep37: Andoni Iraola : PL Stories
programme.desc: Andoni Iraola went from relative obscurity to leading a once relegation-threatened club to its highest ever points tally in the Premier League. We explore how his fearless philosophy, tactical innovation and emotional connection to the game have driven his teams to challenge expectations and rewrite their identity. A story of a Basque footballing icon, and his remarkable journey from Cyprus to the Premier League with Bournemouth in 5 years.

programme.desc: Review brings you all the action from Matchweek 26, featuring the midweek fixtures with Leeds trip to Chelsea, West Ham host Manchester United, and Thursday's fixture as Arsenal take on Brentford in West London.

programme.title: Ep08: Darren Bent: My PL Years : Rewind
programme.desc: Darren Bent is one of a select number of players to have scored a century of goals in the Premier League. The prolific striker recalls his days at Ipswich, Charlton, Spurs, Sunderland, and Aston Villa and the goals he scored on his way to joining that elite group.

programme.title: Tot v Ars : Classic Match

programme.title: Ep32: (Subbed) Micky van De ven : PL Stories
programme.desc: We reflect on the rapid rise of Micky van de Ven, tracing his journey from a promising young defender in the Netherlands to becoming one of the Premier League's most electrifying modern centrebacks. We sit down with van de Ven to explore the resilience, mentality and sheer speed, on and off the pitch that have defined his ascent. Travelling back to the places and people that shaped him, we uncover the grounding influences, bold decisions and breakthrough moments that propelled him to the top of the game.

programme.title: Ep11: (Subbed) Liverpool - The Succession Story : PL Stories
programme.desc: When Arne Slot guided Liverpool to their 20th League title in his debut season, it marked the beginning of a new era, yet echoed a familiar tradition. Explore the rich legacy of Liverpool's managerial transitions, where through decades of change, one constant endures: the club's remarkable ability to evolve and triumph, through seamless succession.

programme.title: Ep13: Adam Lallana: My Premier League Years : Rewind
programme.desc: From the depths of League One to becoming a Premier League and European champion, Adam Lallana emerged as one of English football's standout talents of the 2010s. The midfielder recalls his most memorable matches for Southampton and Liverpool.

programme.title: Ep17: (Subbed) Maya Yoshida : PL Stories
programme.desc: Maya Yoshida quietly became one of the Premier League's most dependable defenders during his years at Southampton, but his influence reached far beyond the pitch. In this episode, we look back at Yoshida's journey from Japan to England's top-flight, his role as a leader for club and country, and the cultural bridge he helped build along the way. Now in the final stages of his playing career with LA Galaxy in the USA, we catch up with him as he looks to inspire the next generation, both in Japan and around the world.

programme.title: 2015/2016 (Lei) : Review Of The Season
programme.desc: A review of all the best goals, action and drama from Premier League seasons past.

programme.title: Ep43: (Subbed) Foxes Fantasy World : PL Stories
programme.desc: After watching their already relegated side lose to the Invincibles on the last day of the 2003/4 Premier League season, some Leicester City fans stayed behind to watch Arsenal lift the trophy at Highbury. Those fans endured ten years in the wilderness, only for Leicester to return to the big time and embark on a rollercoaster couple of years. In that time they completed the great escape after being dead and buried at the foot of the table and then followed that up with the most unthinkable of Premier League triumphs. This is their story, one of sports greatest triumphs, told by those who wrote it.

programme.title: Ep09: Newcastle United - Not In My Lifetime : PL Stories
programme.desc: Newcastle United are a team on the rise under Eddie Howe; a manager quietly rewriting the modern history of the club. With exclusive access and interviews from inside St. James' Park, we uncover the transformation Howe has led, from stabilising the team to delivering silverware and reigniting belief on Tyneside. As the Magpies set their sights on even greater heights, we ask just how far he can take this ambitious, resurgent club.

programme.title: Ep05: Manager Rivalries : PL Stories
programme.desc: We peel back the layers on the Premier League's most iconic managerial rivalries; battles that shaped eras, defined clubs, and captivated fans around the world. From the fierce mind games between Arsene Wenger and Sir Alex Ferguson, to the emotional explosion of Kevin Keegan's title-chasing Newcastle. From the simmering tension and touchline clashes of Mourinho vs. Wenger, to the tactical chess match between Jurgen Klopp and Pep Guardiola. Through exclusive interviews and unforgettable moments, we explore how these rivalries pushed the limits and left a lasting mark on the Premier League.

programme.title: Ep08: Emmanuel Adebayor : PL Moments
programme.desc: Join Togo and African football icon Emmanuel Adebayor as he relives his top 10 Premier League moments. From iconic goals to unforgettable rivalries, this inspiring and entertaining show is packed with candid insights, untold stories, and the passion that defined his career.

programme.title: Ep07: Jimmy Floyd Hasselbaink : PL Moments
programme.desc: Over a nine season spell in the Premier League, Jimmy Floyd Hasselbaink etched his name into footballing folklore as one of the most dynamic goalscorers in the competition's history. Fourth all time in Premier League goals for Chelsea, Hasselbaink's iconic freekicks and powerful finishes have seen him score some of the League's most memorable goals. This week, the Dutch international sits down with PL Moments to break down how to strike the ball, and talk us through his ten favourite moments from his Premier League career.

programme.title: Ep19: (Subbed) Marc Cucurella : The Big Interview
programme.desc: From the training grounds of La Masia, to Stamford Bridge - Marc Cucurella's journey to the top of World Football is a story of self belief and overcomiong adversity. One of the game's great character's - Cucurella grew up a Barcelona fan, and a graduate of their esteemed academy but only made one first team appearace for his childhood club. Stops at Eibar and Getafe led to a move to the Premier League and Brighton where he made his mark, earning an international call up and shortly afterwards - a blockbuster move to Chelsea. This week, Cucurella visits the West End's Dominion Theatre to sit down with the Big Interview and discuss his journey to the Premier League, his intrests away from the pitch and the importance of stay true to yourself.

programme.title: Ep10: (Subbed) Sunderland - 'Return Of The Black Cats' : PL Stories
programme.desc: We delve into the remarkable journey of Sunderland AFC; a club defined by its dramatic highs and painful lows. From their proud top-flight legacy to the heartbreak of consecutive relegations, Sunderland's story is one of resilience, identity, and unbreakable community spirit. Now, under the leadership of new head coach Regis Le Bris, the Black Cats are preparing for a new chapter. With exclusive behind-the-scenes access during their pre-season tour, we go inside the dressing room, onto the training pitch, and into the mindset of a team chasing revival; capturing the passion, pressure, and pride of a club determined to climb back to where it belongs.

Melalui Pengalaman Kecil Seperti Belajar Jujur, Disiplin, Menghormati Orang Tua, Menjaga Shalat, Bersikap Sabar, Dan Tolong-Menolong, Mereka Perlahan Memahami Bahwa Menjadi Muslim Terbaik Bukan Tentang Menjadi Sempurna, Tetapi Tentang Terus Berusaha Memperbaiki Diri. Setiap Episode Menyampaikan Nilai Akhlak, Adab, Dan Keimanan Dengan Cara Ringan, Hangat, Dan Mudah Dipahami Anak-Anak, Sehingga Islam Hadir Sebagai Pedoman Hidup Yang Dekat Dan Menyenangkan.

programme.title: Ibra Berkisah
programme.desc: Ibrahim Atau Ibra Adalah Murid Pesantren Yang Santun Dan Selalu Mengajak Teman-Temannya Untuk Meneladani Nabi Muhammad Saw, Dia Pun Sejak Kecil Sudah Tinggal Di Pesantren. Ibra Memiliki Teman Bernama Tokek Dan Hoho. Tokek Adalah Anak Yang Lucu Dan Periang, Sedangkan Hoho Adalah Seorang Anak Jakarta Yang Dilahirkan Dari Keluarga Kaya Raya, Sifatnya Manja Dan Tidak Mengerti Sama Sekali Tentang Islam. Selama Di Pesantren, Hoho Sekamar Dengan Ibra Yang Mana Di Perkenalan Awal Mereka, Hoho Menganggap Remeh Ibra Yang Dia Anggap Sebagai Anak Kampung. Tapi Ternyata Dari Ibra Lah Hoho Banyak Mendapatkan Pelajaran Hidup Dan Kisah-Kisah Teladan Nabi Muhammad Shalallahu Alaihi Wassalam.

programme.title: Di Ujung Rindu
programme.desc: Program Reality Show Yang Mengangkat Kisah Seseorang Atas Kerinduannya Terhadap Orang Terkasih Dan Memiliki Harapan Dapat Bertemu Serta Mengenang Moment Indah Kebersamaan Mereka. Program Ini Terbagi Dalam Segmen Curhatan Narsum, Reka Adegan, Dan Satgas Rindu.

programme.title: Cahaya Bagi Negeri

programme.title: Riko The Series
programme.desc: Animasi Lokal Yang Mengangkat Keseharian Seorang Anak Bernama Riko Bersama Sahabat Robotnya, Q110 Untuk Menemukan Dan Mempelajari Hal-Hal Baru Disekitarnya. Q110 Bertugas Menjelaskan Kepada Riko Hal-Hal Baru Yang Mereka Temukan. Berkat Q110, Riko Mempelajari Banyak Pengetahuan Soal Ilmuan-Ilmuan Muslim Dari Penjuru Dunia, Kekuasaan Allah Sang Maha Pencipta, Dan Tentunya Banyak Hal Lainya.

programme.title: Marsupilami
programme.desc: Masih Bersama Hector Dantantenya, Diane, Dan Sahabatnya, Marsupilami Dan Keluarganya! Bekerja Sama Menggagalkan Semua Rencana Felicia Untuk Mengubah Hutan Tropis Palombia Menjadi Kota Megapolis Devort. Kaliini, Hector Akan Bertemu Dengan Teman Tak Terduga Dan Mengatasi Berbagai Masalah Yang Dipicu Felicia Dan Para Kaki Tangan Nya!

programme.title: Bread Barbershop
programme.desc: Bread, Seorang Tukang Cukur Jenius, Memecahkan Masalah Penampilan Dengan Keterampilan Memotong Rambutnya Yang Briliant. Sekarang Dia Hadir Untuk Memecahkan Masalah Para Bintang Di Bakery Town. Bertentangan Dengan Penampilan Mereka Yang Glamor Dan Bersinar, Para Selebriti Ini Menjalani Hari Yang Sangat Suram. Bread Dan Keluarganya Siap Membantu Para Selebriti Untuk Menemukan Lagi Kebahagiaan Mereka.

programme.desc: Di Tengah Hutan Belantara, Terdapat Desa Rahasia Dihuni Oleh Sekelompok Makhluk Kecil Berwarna Biru Yang Dipimpin Oleh Papa Smurf. Para Smurf Tinggal Di Rumah Berbentuk Jamur Dan Hidup Dengan Damai. Namun, Kedatangan Penyihir Jahat Gargamel Dan Kucingnya, Azrael, Merusak Kedamaian Desa Tersebut. Sehingga Para Smurf Harus Mencari Cara Agar Tidak Ditangkap Oleh Gargamel Dan Azrael.

programme.title: Boboiboy
programme.desc: Sebuah Program Animasi Yang Mengisahkan Boboiboy Dan Teman-Temannya Yakni Gopal, Ying, Dan Yaya Yang Masing-Masing Memiliki Kekuatan Super. Dengan Kekuatan Yang Dimiliki Mereka Mencegah Adu Du Mencuri Biji Kakao Tok Aba Yang Digunakan Sebagai Sumber Energi. Selain Itu, Boboiboy Dan Teman-Temannya Menjadi Pahlawan Super Dalam Menumpas Kejahatan Dan Menjaga Kedamaian Bumi.

programme.title: Makania
programme.desc: Naz Dan Ayahnya, Kareem, Mengikuti Suatu Kompetisi Memasak Yaitu Makania Next Top Chef (Mantop). Mereka Mengikuti Kompetisi Ini Untuk Memenangkan Hadiah Uang Tunai Yang Besar Dan Menyelamatkan Restoran Mereka. Namun, Ada Sebuah Rahasia Tersembunyi Di Balik Kompetisi Ini.

programme.title: I'M The Best Muslim!
programme.desc: I'M The Best Muslim Adalah Program Animasi Edukasi Islami Anak Yang Mengangkat Kisah Keseharian Anak-Anak Muslim Dalam Belajar Menjadi Pribadi Yang Lebih Baik Menurut Ajaran Islam. Melalui Pengalaman Kecil Seperti Belajar Jujur, Disiplin, Menghormati Orang Tua, Menjaga Shalat, Bersikap Sabar, Dan Tolong-Menolong, Mereka Perlahan Memahami Bahwa Menjadi Muslim Terbaik Bukan Tentang Menjadi Sempurna, Tetapi Tentang Terus Berusaha Memperbaiki Diri. Setiap Episode Menyampaikan Nilai Akhlak, Adab, Dan Keimanan Dengan Cara Ringan, Hangat, Dan Mudah Dipahami Anak-Anak, Sehingga Islam Hadir Sebagai Pedoman Hidup Yang Dekat Dan Menyenangkan.

programme.title: Ibra Berkisah
programme.desc: Ibrahim Atau Ibra Adalah Murid Pesantren Yang Santun Dan Selalu Mengajak Teman-Temannya Untuk Meneladani Nabi Muhammad Saw, Dia Pun Sejak Kecil Sudah Tinggal Di Pesantren. Ibra Memiliki Teman Bernama Tokek Dan Hoho. Tokek Adalah Anak Yang Lucu Dan Periang, Sedangkan Hoho Adalah Seorang Anak Jakarta Yang Dilahirkan Dari Keluarga Kaya Raya, Sifatnya Manja Dan Tidak Mengerti Sama Sekali Tentang Islam. Selama Di Pesantren, Hoho Sekamar Dengan Ibra Yang Mana Di Perkenalan Awal Mereka, Hoho Menganggap Remeh Ibra Yang Dia Anggap Sebagai Anak Kampung. Tapi Ternyata Dari Ibra Lah Hoho Banyak Mendapatkan Pelajaran Hidup Dan Kisah-Kisah Teladan Nabi Muhammad Shalallahu Alaihi Wassalam.

Dimitri terjebak dalam situasi sulit akibat ulah sang adik, Jupiter (Bizael) yang menuduh Dimitri melecehkan Yunita. Hubungan Dimitri dengan Diandra pun semakin merenggang. Tuduhan lainnya juga harus diterima Dimitri sebagai penyebab insiden kecelakaan seorang wanita. Posisi Dimitri semakin terpojok setelah Diandra yang diminta sebagai saksi justru tidak berpihak kepadanya hingga Dimitri mendapat sanksi mendekam di balik jeruji besi selama lima tahun.Lima tahun berlalu, Dimitri hidup bebas dan melanjutkan usaha sang ayah. Ia pun membuka kisah cinta baru dengan Melissa (Tasya Panggabean). Takdir pun berkata lain, pertemuan Dimitri dan Diandra kembali terjadi...kisah selengkapnya, silakan saksikan hanya di SCTV.
